# Commit message & PR description

When asked for a **commit message**, **PR description**, or **merge summary**, follow the canonical templates:

- **PR body** → [`docs/agent/templates/pr-body.md`](../../docs/agent/templates/pr-body.md)
- **Commit message / chat summary** → [`docs/agent/templates/commit-message.md`](../../docs/agent/templates/commit-message.md)

These are the single source of truth. Do not inline or redefine sections here.

## Quick reference

| Output | Template |
| --- | --- |
| GitHub PR description | `pr-body.md` — full markdown layout |
| Git commit | `commit-message.md` — subject + plain-text body |
| Chat-only summary | `commit-message.md` — omit `Closes #…` if no issue |

## Agent Report

Fields are defined in [`docs/agent/values.md#agent-report-canonical-fields`](../../docs/agent/values.md#agent-report-canonical-fields). Copy the 7-bullet block exactly.

## Agent Identification

Every AI-posted PR comment must include the `**Agent:**` line per [`docs/agent/values.md#agent-identification-canonical-format`](../../docs/agent/values.md#agent-identification-canonical-format) — all 3 fields: `tool · model-id · effort`.
